[ ] Allow a lone open-bracket inside description notes $The grammar description text rule excludes the open-bracket char to reserve it for wiki-links, so a bare open-bracket inside a dollar-delimited note ends the text chunk and derails the parse (observed: clearhead add wrote a note containing bracket-at-graph-bracket, then the next parse failed with unexpected token and silently aborted the following add). Treat dollar-delimited note content as opaque except for the closing dollar and real double-bracket links. Fix in grammar.js description rules + regenerate; add a test note containing brackets and braces.$ !2 #019f76e0-ea98-7e73-9301-d7f1d7945722
